AN ACT relating to criminal procedure; revising requirements
relating to certain proceedings in justice court; and
providing other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law requires certain proceedings in a justice court to be recorded by
2 the use of sound recording equipment. (NRS 4.390) Existing law also specifies that
3 if a case is tried by jury in a justice court, a certified court reporter must be present
4 and report on the trial under certain circumstances. (NRS 175.011) Section 4 of this
5 bill eliminates this requirement, thereby authorizing a justice court to record a
6 proceeding before a jury using sound recording equipment under certain
7 circumstances.
8 Existing law provides that sound recordings of certain proceedings in justice
9 court must be preserved for certain periods. (NRS 4.420) Section 5.5 of this bill
10 provides that with respect to certain criminal proceedings in a justice court, sound
11 recordings must be preserved for a period of at least 5 years.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
