14 Sec. 5.5. NRS 4.420 is hereby amended to read as follows:
15 4.420 1. Except as otherwise provided in this section:
16 (a) The sound recording of each proceeding in justice court must
17 be preserved until at least 1 year after the time for filing an appeal
18 expires.
19 (b) With respect to a proceeding in justice court that involves a
20 misdemeanor for which enhanced penalties may be imposed, a gross
21 misdemeanor or a felony, the sound recording of the proceeding
22 must be preserved for at least 8 years after the time for filing an
23 appeal expires.
24 (c) With respect to a preliminary hearing conducted pursuant
25 to NRS 171.178, the sound recording of the proceeding must be
26 preserved for at least 5 years after the date of the preliminary
27 hearing.
28 2. If no appeal is taken, the justice of the peace may order the
29 destruction of the recording at any time after the date specified in
30 subsection 1.
31 3. If there is an appeal to the district court, the sound recording
32 must be preserved until at least 30 days after final disposition of the
33 case on appeal, but the justice of the peace may order the destruction
34 of the recording at any time after that date.
35 Sec. 6. This act becomes effective on July 1, 2025.
